==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chronologer
<hw>Chro*nol"o*ger</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>A person
who investigates dates of events and transactions; one skilled in
chronology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That learned noise and dust of the <qex>chronologist</qex> is
wholly to be avoided.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>THe most exact <qex>chronologers</qex> tell us that Christ was
born in October, and not in December.</q> <rj><qau>John
Knox.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chronology</ent>⟦br⟧
